text: __NOTOC__ Ælfred or Alfred was an Anglo-Saxon Bishop of Selsey. Ælfred attests charters from 943 to 953.Kelly Charters of Selsey p. xci In 945 Ælfred received a grant of land from King Edmund.Anglo-Saxons.net Charters S506 accessed on 25 August 2007 Ælfred died between 953 and 956.Fryde, et al.
